line_1: May learn strict justice 'mongst their dolls to deal,
line_2: May learn forbearance, and may learn to feel,

line_1: Let muckworms, who in dirty acres deal,
line_2: Lament those hardships which we cannot feel.
The sense to see and feel.

line_1: No costly lord the sumptuous banquet deal
line_2: To make him loath his vegetable meal;
Teach me but once like him to feel:

line_1: Who only with the moderns deal?
line_2: Then where? from whom? what can I steal,
Teach me but once like him to feel:

line_1: Seek ye to thrive? In flatt'ry deal,
line_2: Your scorn, your hate, with that conceal;
